NUMBER 3753
NAME Herbie's Hideway, home sweet home
INDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
Twigs and leaves are spread out on the floor of this entranceway to the
cottage to mimic the footing of most of Grymwood. Small, dirty drakin
footprints and the pleasing aroma of various herbs and blossoms are
everywhere. The woodsy walls, natural flooring and overall aura of the
room makes you feel as though you are in a most pleasant section of woods,
perhaps a little paradise. There is an oak door to the west, a mirmach
door to the north, a large mahogany door to the east, and a teak door that
leads out. A comfy couch here is flanked by some shelves, a coffee table
and a small cabinet. On top of the shelves, you see some reading material.
*DESCRIPTION_END
